value.value: A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands include CCL17 and CCL22.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands include CCL3, CCL4, CCL5, CCL8, CCL14.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CCL20.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR7 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are CCL19 and CCL21.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands include CCL1, CCL4, CCL17.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCR9 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CCL25.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CX3CR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CX3CL1.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CXCR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands include CXCL9, CXCL10, CXCL11.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CXCR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CXCL12.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CXCR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CXCL13.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CXCR6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is CXCL16.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human ACKR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand may be CXCL12. No signaling pathway has been identified.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human XCR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are XCL1 and XCL2.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human ACKR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands may be CCL19, CCL21, CCL25. This is a non-signaling chemokine receptor.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human CCRL2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands may be CCL2, CCL5, CCL7, CCL8. The signaling pathway is not known.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human ACKR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands may be CCL2, CCL3, CCL5, CCL7. The signaling pathway is not known.

A cholecystokinin receptor that is a translation product of the human CCKAR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is sulfated CCK, which is bound with a 500- to 1000-fold higher affinity than sulfated gastrin or nonsulfated CCK.

A cholecystokinin receptor that is a translation product of the human CCKBR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The active receptor binds sulfated and non-sulfated forms of gastrin and CCK and their analogs.
A cysteinyl leukotriene receptor that is a translation product of the human CYSLTR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is the cysteinyl leukotriene D4.
A cysteinyl leukotriene receptor that is a translation product of the human CYSLTR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is the cysteinyl leukotriene C4.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human OPN3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An endothelin receptor that is a translation product of the human EDNRA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The active form binds endothelin 1 (ET-1) and ET-2 with much higher affinity than ET-3.
An endothelin receptor that is a translation product of the human EDNRB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The active form binds endothelin 1 (ET-1), ET-2, and ET-3 with equal affinity.
A bombesin receptor that is a translation product of the human GRPR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is gastrin releasing peptide.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human OPN1MW, OPN1MW2, or OPN1MW3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=gene. Note: The human OPN1MW, OPN1MW2, and OPN1MW3 genes encode identical proteins.

value.value: A growth hormone secretagogue/motilin receptor that is a translation product of the human GHSR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Although its preferred ligand is ghrelin, it also binds other growth hormone releasing peptides and some nonpeptide ligands.
A chemokine receptor whose active form binds interleukin-8 with high affinity.

An interleukin-1 alpha that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P01583-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

An interleukin-1 receptor antagonist protein that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P18510-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

An interleukin-1 receptor antagonist protein that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P18510-4 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A melanocortin receptor that is a translation product of the human MC5R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A melanocortin receptor that is a translation product of the human MC1R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A growth hormone secretagogue/motilin receptor that is a translation product of the human MLNR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is motilin, an intestinal peptide that stimulates contraction of gut smooth muscle.
A bombesin receptor that is a translation product of the human NMBR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is neuromedin-B.
A tachykinin receptor that is a translation product of the human TACR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is neurokinin B, also known as neuromedin-K.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human OPN4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human OPN1LW gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human RHO gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A tachykinin receptor that is a translation product of the human TACR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is neurokinin A, also known as substance-K.
A tachykinin receptor that is a translation product of the human TACR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is substance-P.
An animal opsin that is a translation product of the human RRH gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: CD2 molecule isoform 1, signal peptide removed N-glycosylated 1

value.value: A CD2 molecule isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been N-glycosylated. The N-glycosylation seems to be essential for adhesion functions. Example: UniProtKB:P06729-1, 25-351, Asn-89, MOD:00160.

label.value: alpha-latrotoxin isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: An alpha-latrotoxin isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the secreted form.
